included.title: Head of Data Science, Vertical Products

included.description:
I learned how to run a Sales BI / Sales Operation team with one of the largest sales platforms in the world. I brought three initiatives to support the team and successfully executed on all three:

* Established project management process: analysts suffer from the flood of requests coming in, partners complain about their projects not being done quickly. We put all requests in the system, prioritize every week and then communicate with our partners. Sales managers can request to change prioritization, so they feel in control. Analysts feel ownership by recommending their own priorities and managing the relationship with sales managers;

* Apply advanced analytics techniques to improve targeting and seller understanding: started to build lead generation models for targeting; started to build LTV (Life Time Value) models to better understand our sellers;

* Introduced and implemented self-service tools: lead Amazon in implementing a Tableau based self-service reporting system that's accurate, updated and user friendly for sales managers to use; 

My team provided analytics support in ETL, data model, reports, ad-hoc analysis, data self-service tools and advanced analytics for the North American Sales organization (seller acquisition & management) at Amazon. I was fortunate for the opportunity to work alongside a lot of smart an driven individuals

Team I supported includes:
Marketplace - Direct Sales
Marketplace - Self-Service Registration
Marketplace - On-boarding
Global Selling
Account Management
Fulfill by Amazon

3-D printing

included.title: Director, Data Science

included.description:
It was my privilege to grow with a successful start-up like Riot Games. I was impressed every day by how smart and mission-driven my co-workers are. I learned how to build/develop a team, and later a discipline with a growing company, I get to know different functions within a tech start-up, and how analytics supports them. I learned how to develop managers, and work with cross-functional teams. My team covered analytics supporting marketing, game, product and website.

Built and lead a 10+ persons team of analytics experts to provide reporting, data analytics, data self-service tools and preditive modeling solutions to better understand and service the 30MM+ global users of the "most played PC game in the world" (Forbes) - "League of Legends". 

Promote using data and analytics to make informed decisions at all levels of the organization. 

Received a promotion from Manager to Senior Manager after one year at the job.

Designed the framework of the analytics descipline:

Central Intelligence - focus on company-wide reporting that goes to senior management, as well as ad-hoc requests;

Embedded team - mid to senior level analysts who embed into each product teams, becoming trusted advisers to the product team leaders;

Data Science - focuses on long-term large projects that require deep statistical knowledge. Work includes player segmentation, revenue model, champion / skin sales models, social network analysis, text minding for toxic players, card game simulation, CRM lead generation, etc.

Supporting departments includes: Marketing / Direct Marketing, Production, Design, Live Design, E-Commerce, Store, Platform, International, Community, Player Support, Finance, etc.

Supporting markets includes: North America, Europe-West, Europe - Nordic East, China, Southeast Asia, Korea, Brazil, Turkey, etc.
